to the editor arafat says plan outlined by saudi needs us backing front page feb 28 about the growing support for crown prince abdullah 's proposal for full pan arab acceptance of israel in return for the establishment of a palestinian state in the west bank and gaza demonstrates the urgency of our own government 's seizing this opportunity to jump start israeli palestinian negotiations the saudi plan is still in its most tentative stage one does not have to agree with it in full to recognize that it a significant step especially when one considers the 50 year record of saudi hostility to the idea of a jewish state president bush and secretary of state colin l powell have already responded positively vice president dick cheney should use his mideast trip this month to explore the most effective way for america to advance this promising initiative judith stern peck president israel policy forum new york march 1 2002

